167456;"Welcome Letter";"N48";"PLL_RECORD";"Cases";"Thank you for choosing Florida Insurance Law Group [$(record : case_id)$]";"

ATTORNEY-CLIENT PRIVILEGE
$(record : insured)$
Ins. Co.: $(record : insurance_company)$
Case ID: $(record : case_id)$
$(record : insured)$,

Greetings.  Thank you for choosing Florida Insurance Law Group to assist you in recovering insurance benefits relating to your insurance claim. Here at Florida Insurance Law Group, we are dedicated to providing you the best possible service while working diligently to ensure that you receive all of the benefits you are entitled to under your insurance policy.  Whether we are representing you during the initial adjustment of the claim or during the litigation of the case we will do our best keep you up to date with any major changes in your case.  Many of these updates will be sent to the email you provided Please keep in mind that insurance claims are not typically resolved quickly but rather take time to obtain the results you are looking for. While we endeavor to put pressure on the Insurance Company to issue payment as quickly as possible, the actual amount of time it takes to resolve a claim is dependent on a variety of factors, many of which are beyond our control. For instance, if your claim was recently reported to your insurance company, by law, they have 90 days to adjust your claim and decide whether they will provide coverage or deny your claim. If your claim is readily for litigation, our office must provide your insurance company with a notice of litigation which provides them 14 days to settle, demand mediation or appraisal, or even request additional inspections before we can file a lawsuit. You can rest assured that the team of professionals assigned to your case are doing everything they can to make sure this is as quick and effective process as possible.

Should you have any questions during our representation of your claim, please feel free to contact us at (305) 906-4262 or HOS@flinslaw.com. When calling please note the Case ID listed above. This Case ID is our internal case management number which allows our team to quickly locate our claim in our case management system allowing us to provide you the most up to date information and direct you to the team member who can best assist you with your question or issue. Once again, thank you for choosing Florida Insurance Law Group, we look forward to working with you.

column4: Robert F. Gonzalez, Esq.
Managing Attorney

167473;"10 Day Demand Payment Closing Letter";"N49";"PLL_RECORD";"Cases";"Closing Letter re: $(record : case_id)$ $(record : provider)$ aao $(record : insured)$";"
ATTORNEY-CLIENT PRIVILEGE
$(record : provider)$ a/a/o $(record : insured)$ v. $(record : insurance_company)$
Case ID: $(record : case_id)$
Claim Number: $(record : claim_number)$
$(record : ps_corporate_rep)$,

Please be advised that our office has received payment for the services rendered by your company in the above-referenced matter.  As we previously notified you, our office sent a Notice of Intent to Litigate to $(record : insurance_company)$ seeking payment for your outstanding invoice(s) as required under Fla. Stat. §627.7152. In response to the Notice of Intent to Litigate, $(record : insurance_company)$ issued payment for same. Since there is no longer a controversy between your company and $(record : insurance_company)$ regarding this matter, we will be forwarding said payment to you or the appropriate receiver as per our standing instructions and closing our file regarding this matter. We thank you for choosing Florida Insurance Law Group regarding this matter and look forward to working with you again in the future.
Should you have any questions, please feel free to contact us at (305) 906-4262 or intake@flinslaw.com.
Sincerely,

column4: Robert F. Gonzalez, Esq.
Managing Attorney

292995;"Circulation Letter";"N143";"PLL_RECORD";"Cases";"Circulation Letter";"Dear $(record : ho_attorney)$,
I hope this email finds you well,

Through an agreement between ClaimPay and its affiliates and $(record : provider)$, ClaimPay has acquired a beneficial interest in claim $(record : claim_number)$ “Claim” involving your client $(record : insured)$. In essence, ClaimPay has stepped into the shoes of $(record : provider)$ with respect to collecting all sums due and owing for the services rendered by $(record : provider)$ and settlement authority on behalf of  $(record : provider)$.  Additionally, enclosed herein is a Direction to Pay and Letter of Protection, executed by your client. Please provide acknowledgement of your receipt of the Direction to Pay and Letter of Protection document.
To keep a fluid and professional relationship, ClaimPay requests that you comply with the following guidelines:

column2: • In addition to providing an updated status of the above referenced claim as soon as feasible, please provide a status update every 60 days, which should include details as to the movement of the claim.  The update can be brief, and there’s no need for a detailed summary. Updates including but not limited to statuses such as, “in pre-suit stage,” “litigation initiated” “approaching settlement,” “settled and awaiting payment,” “settlement payment received,” “case dismissed” etc. will suffice. Further, please provide the case number and county of filing if you have initiated litigation of the Claim.
• Contact Jesse Schwartz or Wilfredo Navarro at Jesse@claimpay.net or Wilfredo@claimpay.net, to obtain settlement authority for the collection of $(record : provider)$’s invoice(s).
• All settlement checks or payments for the benefit of $(record : provider)$ must be mailed directly to our office at: 6330 Manor Lane, Suite 200, Miami, FL 33143.

column1: Your cooperation and adherence to our guidelines will help maintain a positive relationship between our organizations.  We have built excellent relationships with law firms that handle claims involving ClaimPay’s clients, and we are confident that working with your team will be equally successful. If you have any questions, please don’t hesitate to contact me at any time.
Sincerely,
______________________________
Jesse Schwartz Esq.
General Counsel
Jesse@claimpay.net
